WEBVTT

00:02.680 --> 00:04.680
<i>My name is Brilliant Chang.</i>

00:04.800 --> 00:06.200
Mr Thomas...

00:06.320 --> 00:08.160
(SNIFFS)

00:08.280 --> 00:12.200
...it is the purest opium
that has ever arrived in Europe.

00:12.320 --> 00:16.120
Came off a ship called the <i>Capital,</i>
out of Shanghai.

00:16.240 --> 00:17.960
This is a gift, Mr Shelby.

00:18.080 --> 00:21.840
Canals are the idea, right, Chang?

00:21.960 --> 00:25.640
I believe we've friends in common.
We should postpone our war.

00:25.760 --> 00:29.000
Your message said you wanted to seal
our truce with some business.

00:29.120 --> 00:32.240
I'm involved in a transaction
with Jimmy McCavern.

00:32.360 --> 00:35.040
I need your signature as a guarantor
on the transaction

00:35.160 --> 00:38.320
should his cheque fail to be honoured.

00:38.440 --> 00:41.360
The war with the Billy Boys is postponed.
We've made peace.

00:41.480 --> 00:42.960
We're gonna do business together.

00:44.680 --> 00:46.720
THOMAS: <i>There's a part of me
that is unfamiliar to myself</i>

00:46.840 --> 00:49.720
<i>and I keep finding myself there.</i>

00:49.840 --> 00:52.480
<i>And only</i> the January
<i>can get me away.</i>

00:58.160 --> 01:02.560
LINDA: His name was Frederick.
All we ever did was talk, Arthur.

01:02.680 --> 01:05.960
He just listened.
And now he has no face.

01:08.000 --> 01:09.920
May you Peaky Blinders all rot...

01:10.040 --> 01:11.840
(GUNSHOT)

01:21.680 --> 01:23.560
- Clear that shit. Clear it!
- All right.

01:23.680 --> 01:24.920
Take her.

01:34.720 --> 01:36.440
(LINDA GROANS)

01:38.920 --> 01:42.320
Go outside. Till it's done.
Till it's done, brother.

01:42.440 --> 01:44.880
(LINDA GROANS AND PANTS)

01:47.400 --> 01:50.240
Linda, I would have taken your bullet.

01:51.320 --> 01:52.800
I deserved the bullet.

01:52.920 --> 01:55.520
An eye for an eye and a tooth for a tooth!

01:55.640 --> 01:57.480
(GROANS)

01:57.600 --> 01:58.640
Linda!

01:58.760 --> 01:59.960
Linda, look at me.

02:00.080 --> 02:01.640
Linda, you've got a kid.

02:01.760 --> 02:04.440
If you die, he'll come to us to raise.

02:04.560 --> 02:05.800
You hear me?

02:07.360 --> 02:09.000
I used a derringer.

02:09.120 --> 02:10.720
- Shh!
- Right.

02:10.840 --> 02:11.960
- Shh!
- It's still in there.

02:12.080 --> 02:13.480
It's above the bone.

02:13.600 --> 02:15.240
MOSLEY: Mr Shelby, your guests.

02:15.360 --> 02:16.600
Get him out. Arthur!

02:16.720 --> 02:19.080
Family only. Get him out!

02:20.800 --> 02:22.600
- Mr Shelby...
- Get out!

02:24.120 --> 02:25.440
Get out!

02:26.600 --> 02:30.040
Lizzie, go to the kitchen
and get some iodine. Now! Go!

02:32.000 --> 02:34.600
- Shh...
- (LINDA MUTTERS)

02:35.760 --> 02:37.000
Linda...

02:37.120 --> 02:38.600
You'll have to bite on this.

02:38.720 --> 02:41.120
- Linda... Arthur.
- Bite! Come here.

02:41.240 --> 02:43.320
Now, it's really gonna hurt.

02:43.440 --> 02:44.960
(MUFFLED GASPS)

02:45.080 --> 02:46.600
One, two, three...

02:46.720 --> 02:49.320
(MUFFLED SCREAM)

02:50.920 --> 02:53.000
(GASPS AND WAILS)

02:53.120 --> 02:54.520
(BULLET CLATTERS)

02:54.640 --> 02:56.280
You're all right. You're all right.

02:56.400 --> 02:58.640
- It's all over.
- Hold her.

02:58.760 --> 03:00.720
(SCREAMS)

03:06.640 --> 03:10.240
Is she going to be all right, Tom?
Is she going to be all right, Tom?

03:10.360 --> 03:11.440
Yeah.

03:11.560 --> 03:12.840
Oh, Jesus.

03:12.960 --> 03:14.280
Arthur, come here. Come here.

03:14.400 --> 03:17.520
If you love her, go to the library,
get some opium.

03:17.640 --> 03:20.040
- Go on. She'll be fine. Go sort it.
- Right.

03:21.360 --> 03:22.680
(EXHALES)

03:25.560 --> 03:28.440
Actually, you can use mine.

03:33.160 --> 03:36.880
Brought a bit to celebrate
the wedding proposal.

03:38.160 --> 03:39.960
Oh! He proposed, eh?

03:42.360 --> 03:43.680
One knee.

03:45.200 --> 03:47.520
Congratulations, Poll.

03:47.640 --> 03:48.600
Linda...

03:48.720 --> 03:50.200
Linda...

03:50.320 --> 03:52.000
- You're gonna have to drink this.
- No.

03:52.120 --> 03:53.560
I don't want anything you've touched.

03:53.680 --> 03:56.800
25 seconds. 25 seconds
and the pain will be gone.

03:56.920 --> 03:58.800
Even the pain in your head.

03:58.920 --> 04:00.400
Right, here you go. Drink.

04:07.200 --> 04:08.440
Cushion, Poll.

04:12.080 --> 04:13.440
Right.

04:18.840 --> 04:20.280
Oh, Jesus Christ...

04:20.400 --> 04:22.200
- (SOBS)
- Arthur...

04:23.280 --> 04:24.840
She's gonna be fine.

04:24.960 --> 04:27.920
I gave her something
to get her to sleep.

04:28.040 --> 04:29.320
She's gonna be fine.

04:32.400 --> 04:36.000
You should have... You should have
let her do it, Poll.

04:36.120 --> 04:38.160
You should have let her do it.

04:39.440 --> 04:40.760
Arthur...

04:42.040 --> 04:43.560
You should have let her do it.

04:43.680 --> 04:45.400
Look at me, brother! Look at me!

04:45.520 --> 04:47.360
You've got things to do.

04:47.480 --> 04:48.960
You've got a kid.

04:49.080 --> 04:50.920
- Yeah.
- We need you!

04:51.040 --> 04:53.280
- All right? You understand?
- Yeah.

04:53.400 --> 04:55.960
Aberama wants you as best man.

04:56.080 --> 04:57.200
You hear that?

05:00.800 --> 05:03.160
I save his life, he hugs him.

05:06.160 --> 05:07.280
Oh...

05:08.480 --> 05:10.000
I'll do it.

05:10.120 --> 05:11.440
No take.

05:12.640 --> 05:14.640
Right, fine. Let him be. Let him be.

05:24.240 --> 05:26.040
MOSLEY: Ladies and gentlemen...

05:27.920 --> 05:29.080
Ladies and gentlemen...

05:30.520 --> 05:34.600
...I would like to extend our gratitude
to the musicians

05:34.720 --> 05:37.760
and the dance company
for your wonderful performance.

05:37.880 --> 05:38.840
Hear hear!

05:38.960 --> 05:42.680
This has been a wonderful evening.

05:44.240 --> 05:47.360
And not only
for the music and the dancing.

05:47.480 --> 05:51.280
It has also been about us,
the people gathered here.

05:52.640 --> 05:55.560
English people
in the very heart of England.

05:55.680 --> 05:57.120
(MURMURS OF AGREEMENT)

05:57.240 --> 06:00.000
There are no people
I would rather be among,

06:00.120 --> 06:04.480
no place I would rather be
and no time I would rather be alive,

06:04.600 --> 06:07.400
because ever since
the terrible events of October,

06:07.520 --> 06:09.760
when the money markets betrayed us all...

06:09.880 --> 06:11.080
(MURMURS OF AGREEMENT)

06:11.200 --> 06:15.080
...I have known that change is coming.

06:17.400 --> 06:22.800
The human species has never faced
such immense possibilities,

06:22.920 --> 06:24.120
such choices.

06:25.560 --> 06:27.280
In the lives of great nations...

06:29.320 --> 06:31.440
...there are moments of destiny...

06:32.720 --> 06:37.120
...which have swept aside
small men of convention

06:37.240 --> 06:39.320
and discovered men of the moment.

06:39.440 --> 06:44.080
- Hear hear!
- And our host is such a man.

06:44.200 --> 06:45.800
(APPLAUSE)

06:45.920 --> 06:47.560
- For him...
- (APPLAUSE CONTINUES)

06:47.680 --> 06:52.320
For him, the little calculations
of little men mean nothing.

06:54.120 --> 06:58.160
He is a man well suited to
the mighty mood that England is now in.

06:58.280 --> 07:00.120
(MURMURS OF AGREEMENT)

07:00.240 --> 07:03.280
The only reason I say this now,

07:03.400 --> 07:06.480
at this moment, on this stage,

07:06.600 --> 07:09.880
is because I have some news.

07:10.000 --> 07:12.320
- (ALL MURMUR)
- Good news, I think.

07:12.440 --> 07:13.520
(LAUGHTER)

07:15.160 --> 07:18.040
I'm sure our host will forgive me
if I use this platform,

07:18.160 --> 07:23.120
this gathering of friends and like minds,
to give you, his trusted allies,

07:23.240 --> 07:25.880
an early announcement
of a long-overdue event.

07:27.440 --> 07:29.440
I want to tell you good folk first...

07:30.960 --> 07:33.080
...that with the dawn of a new decade...

07:34.640 --> 07:37.080
...I will be setting a new course.

07:37.200 --> 07:42.600
Setting up a new political movement
here in the very heart of England.

07:42.720 --> 07:45.240
And Mr Shelby will be with me,

07:45.360 --> 07:46.960
shoulder to shoulder.

07:47.080 --> 07:48.640
Hear hear!

07:50.760 --> 07:54.520
It will offer
a new conception of politics

07:54.640 --> 07:56.680
in which the great character
of the British,

07:56.800 --> 07:59.120
our true character,

07:59.240 --> 08:01.400
will be reborn.

08:08.400 --> 08:11.920
Many of you lost fortunes
in the recent stock market crash.

08:12.040 --> 08:14.480
The men of money,

08:14.600 --> 08:16.960
the capitalists in New York,

08:17.080 --> 08:18.720
the Jews...

08:19.920 --> 08:22.920
...the money-power, they...they run
an international system

08:23.040 --> 08:24.840
in which the infinite mobility of money,

08:24.960 --> 08:28.680
its capacity to create financial chaos
and panic,

08:28.800 --> 08:33.680
can bring down any government
that dares for one moment to oppose it.

08:35.760 --> 08:40.080
For generations,
the efforts of hard-working men like you

08:40.200 --> 08:43.440
have equipped our competitors against us.

08:43.560 --> 08:45.080
The cotton mills of India.

08:45.200 --> 08:46.800
The cotton mills of Asia.

08:46.920 --> 08:48.880
Created with British money

08:49.000 --> 08:52.520
but used for the destruction
of Lancashire and Yorkshire!

08:52.640 --> 08:54.080
Disgraceful!

08:54.200 --> 08:59.000
The usurers of New York,
the sweated lab our of the Orient

08:59.120 --> 09:03.080
combining to destroy
the iron and steel factories

09:03.200 --> 09:05.400
of Warwickshire and Staffordshire.

09:05.520 --> 09:09.560
These are policies that could not
be pursued by British statesmen

09:09.680 --> 09:14.200
unless they were mad
or the servants of Jewish finance!

09:14.320 --> 09:16.080
(SHOUTS OF AGREEMENT)

09:16.200 --> 09:19.440
<i>They are</i> the ones who took your money,

09:19.560 --> 09:21.800
but it is I and those who know this truth

09:21.920 --> 09:26.520
who will light a flame
the atheists cannot extinguish!

09:26.640 --> 09:28.880
(SHOUTS OF AGREEMENT)

09:36.680 --> 09:39.480
The ranks of our heroes
of the Great War

09:39.600 --> 09:43.880
have been betrayed
again and again by politicians!

09:44.000 --> 09:49.760
But hear this - those of you who fought
the Jew war for nothing,

09:49.880 --> 09:52.000
you brave men,

09:52.120 --> 09:55.360
you will join hands
with the angry youth of Birmingham

09:55.480 --> 09:58.280
and Manchester and London
and Liverpool

09:58.400 --> 10:02.320
and declare that England lives tonight

10:02.440 --> 10:04.640
and marches on!

10:05.840 --> 10:06.840
Well said!

10:06.960 --> 10:09.640
I say all this to you now...

10:10.760 --> 10:12.560
...because I believe
it is in places like this,

10:12.680 --> 10:17.400
with people like you, that we will have
to pass on our message directly.

10:17.520 --> 10:20.320
Our message can be summarised
with these words -

10:20.440 --> 10:22.520
Britain first.

10:22.640 --> 10:24.480
(CHEERING)

10:28.600 --> 10:31.040
And because this is our message,

10:31.160 --> 10:33.520
I doubt it'll be reported
fairly in the press.

10:33.640 --> 10:37.040
I'm afraid the newspapers of this country

10:37.160 --> 10:42.120
are owned by the same vested interests
who took your money.

10:43.600 --> 10:45.920
They sell to the people false news...

10:46.040 --> 10:48.920
...to raise the interests of the faction
and the section

10:49.040 --> 10:51.120
above the interests of the nation.

10:51.240 --> 10:54.080
- Good man!
- So hear my words

10:54.200 --> 10:57.720
and pass them on
to those with ears to hear.

10:57.840 --> 11:01.800
And be reminded
that when the new decade begins,

11:01.920 --> 11:05.720
there will be the birth
of a new political party

11:05.840 --> 11:07.720
which will speak <i>for you.</i>

11:07.840 --> 11:09.640
(SHOUTS OF ENCOURAGEMENT)

11:09.760 --> 11:11.160
Well said, sir.

11:11.280 --> 11:12.360
Well said!

11:12.480 --> 11:16.720
This party, this new movement,
this revolution...

11:17.840 --> 11:22.680
...will be called
the British Union of Fascists.

11:22.800 --> 11:24.200
Bravo!

11:37.040 --> 11:38.360
Good man!

11:38.480 --> 11:42.000
What the fuck are you doing,
dealing with a man like that, Tommy?

11:42.120 --> 11:44.960
Yep.
You're going to have to trust me.

11:45.080 --> 11:46.360
Again.

11:46.480 --> 11:48.000
(CLEARS HIS THROAT)

11:54.120 --> 11:56.120
I'm going to fuck the swan.

11:58.080 --> 12:00.680
Somebody go and tell her
to come to my room.

12:00.800 --> 12:02.440
How do you know she'll come?

12:04.840 --> 12:06.520
Because they always do.

12:17.880 --> 12:19.640
Now, forgive me.

12:19.760 --> 12:21.960
I'm going to borrow your husband
for a little while.

12:23.760 --> 12:25.080
This way.

12:28.640 --> 12:33.920
Things like tonight, that shooting,
a family dispute in public,

12:34.040 --> 12:36.440
things like that will have to stop.

12:36.560 --> 12:38.280
It's very lower class.

12:38.400 --> 12:40.720
It's all been cleared up, Mr Mosley.

12:50.280 --> 12:53.040
So, did you learn anything
from my speech tonight?

12:53.160 --> 12:54.880
Yes.

12:55.000 --> 12:56.400
Yes, I learned many things.

12:56.520 --> 12:59.720
MOSLEY: Religion was a beast,
but it's dead.

13:00.920 --> 13:03.280
You have to ride the new thing
when it comes.

13:03.400 --> 13:05.040
Like a horse.

13:06.120 --> 13:07.320
You grab it.

13:09.400 --> 13:12.280
I looked into the audience
and I saw medals

13:12.400 --> 13:14.360
and Savile Row suits,

13:14.480 --> 13:15.760
and bitterness.

13:17.960 --> 13:20.640
<i>They are</i> my people.
Your people will be different.

13:23.960 --> 13:26.320
Oh, do see the funny side, Shelby.

13:28.200 --> 13:29.560
I do.

13:31.480 --> 13:33.240
I do see the funny side.

13:39.960 --> 13:41.720
Do you enjoy strategies?

13:41.840 --> 13:44.080
Yes, I do.

13:44.200 --> 13:46.480
Things will begin to happen now.

13:46.600 --> 13:47.800
So...

13:49.160 --> 13:51.720
...there are some things
we need to discuss.

13:51.840 --> 13:54.400
I've been looking
into your companies.

13:54.520 --> 13:58.200
The Shelby portfolio.

13:58.320 --> 14:00.760
Your company lawyer is a Jew.

14:00.880 --> 14:02.440
He will have to go.

14:04.640 --> 14:06.320
Of course.

14:06.440 --> 14:08.800
Also, our friend Jimmy McCavern

14:08.920 --> 14:13.800
has asked for control of the racecourses
north of Wincanton.

14:13.920 --> 14:16.840
I decided it is a trifling thing,
considering our new enterprise,

14:16.960 --> 14:20.160
so I said yes.

14:22.760 --> 14:25.040
In return for what?

14:25.160 --> 14:26.920
No return.

14:30.200 --> 14:31.560
None.

14:34.080 --> 14:38.480
When our campaign begins, the country
will be divided into distinct areas.

14:38.600 --> 14:41.680
McCavern and his men
will be our soldiers in the north,

14:41.800 --> 14:44.160
controlling rallies
and breaking up demonstrations.

14:44.280 --> 14:47.400
In the Midlands, it'll be you.

14:47.520 --> 14:52.080
The south... Well, I have yet to decide.

14:54.720 --> 14:58.360
Please understand what I'm offering you
as we go forward, Mr Shelby.

14:58.480 --> 15:02.800
When we succeed,
even the King will not be above us.

15:10.040 --> 15:11.280
Power.

15:12.360 --> 15:14.360
Like plugging into the mains.

15:15.840 --> 15:17.440
A lighthouse beam.

15:18.560 --> 15:21.440
Your millions of dollars
safe in Switzerland,

15:21.560 --> 15:25.160
and access to every dirty-minded swan
in England.

15:31.360 --> 15:35.400
Oh, and also, Shelby...drink less.

16:21.440 --> 16:23.160
Put it on.

16:25.480 --> 16:28.400
Put the costume back on.

16:46.120 --> 16:47.760
(LAUGHTER)

17:00.040 --> 17:03.360
The ballerina and I were wondering
whether perhaps...

17:04.560 --> 17:06.440
...you might want to join us.

17:06.560 --> 17:08.920
If I told Tommy,
you wouldn't see the morning.

17:09.040 --> 17:11.040
Oh, I doubt that very much.

17:12.080 --> 17:15.520
You see, he is being seduced,
just as you were.

17:27.560 --> 17:29.640
- (DOOR CLOSES)
- (KEY TURNS IN LOCK)

17:30.760 --> 17:31.800
LIZZIE: Tommy.

17:33.800 --> 17:35.360
Tommy!

17:36.640 --> 17:38.720
- Tom!
- (SHOUTS) What?

17:39.800 --> 17:41.960
Lizzie... (SHOUTS) What?!

17:43.640 --> 17:44.800
(SIGHS)

17:44.920 --> 17:46.600
LIZZIE: Tommy, I swear to God, you're bad.

17:46.720 --> 17:48.880
That man is fucking evil.

17:49.000 --> 17:50.200
Lizzie...

17:51.960 --> 17:53.560
I'm only doing this...

17:53.680 --> 17:55.360
...to bring the bastard down.

17:55.480 --> 17:57.920
LIZZIE: Yeah, but why?

17:59.240 --> 18:01.240
Tommy? Why?

18:02.720 --> 18:04.840
I am supplying the British Government

18:04.960 --> 18:08.880
with information on his organisation,

18:09.000 --> 18:14.360
and in return, they are giving me
favourable terms on defence contracts.

18:14.480 --> 18:15.880
No.

18:16.960 --> 18:19.720
You're doing it because you think
somebody should stop him.

18:19.840 --> 18:21.480
I saw your face when he was speaking.

18:23.600 --> 18:26.000
You're doing it because you think
it's the right thing to do.

18:26.120 --> 18:28.800
All this time, you just did things
that feel nice...

18:28.920 --> 18:30.640
...because you can afford it.

18:30.760 --> 18:33.720
Lizzie, please. Please. Please stop.

18:36.200 --> 18:37.520
Don't scare me...

18:38.840 --> 18:41.640
...by saying you see things in my face.

18:42.880 --> 18:45.080
I still want things that feel nice.

18:50.280 --> 18:52.600
<i>(LONG SIGH)</i>

18:52.920 --> 18:54.920
(GASPING)

19:04.560 --> 19:05.920
(LINDA MOANS)

19:06.040 --> 19:07.240
Linda...

19:09.400 --> 19:10.880
Shh. Shh.

19:14.880 --> 19:16.360
Linda...

19:18.360 --> 19:19.600
Let's go.

19:19.720 --> 19:20.720
Hmm?

19:20.840 --> 19:22.800
Let's go, let's leave.

19:24.320 --> 19:27.240
Let's get in the car.
We'll go and pick up Billy.

19:29.040 --> 19:30.960
We'll drive to the docks.

19:31.080 --> 19:32.480
Any dock you want.

19:35.200 --> 19:36.680
We'll get on a boat.

19:36.800 --> 19:38.320
We'll sail away.

19:38.440 --> 19:39.760
You and me.

19:41.440 --> 19:43.000
Any destination.

19:50.600 --> 19:52.200
Be careful, it's...

19:52.320 --> 19:53.880
It's broken everywhere.

19:57.040 --> 19:59.160
We leave tonight. Hmm?

20:00.760 --> 20:02.520
We'd leave this place.

20:02.640 --> 20:04.280
We never come back, Linda.

20:05.640 --> 20:07.200
We never come back.

20:08.360 --> 20:09.960
I mean that.

20:13.840 --> 20:15.720
We go before it gets light.

20:18.280 --> 20:19.640
Say yes.

20:21.280 --> 20:22.880
I've got a better idea.

20:26.440 --> 20:27.840
You stay here...

20:29.400 --> 20:31.640
...living inside your head.

20:33.440 --> 20:35.880
Inside your life. Inside your war.

20:43.720 --> 20:46.440
I'm glad I didn't shoot you.

20:50.640 --> 20:52.760
It would have been a kindness.

21:01.600 --> 21:04.120
Now get out.

21:06.280 --> 21:07.640
Please...

21:22.520 --> 21:24.920
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

22:20.240 --> 22:23.240
An evening with a bunch
of fucking Gypsies.

22:46.760 --> 22:48.640
(CHILDREN PLAYING)

22:50.120 --> 22:51.840
Peter! Peter! Kick it here!

22:57.960 --> 22:59.760
Kick it here, mister!

23:08.760 --> 23:11.960
This is a cheque guarantee,
signed by Mosley...

23:13.200 --> 23:16.040
...on behalf of a man
called Jimmy McCavern.

23:16.160 --> 23:17.600
A cheque for what?

23:17.720 --> 23:20.720
Well, I said it was
for the sale of a gin distillery.

23:20.840 --> 23:22.480
But it doesn't matter.

23:24.000 --> 23:26.360
It is direct evidence of a link
between Mosley

23:26.480 --> 23:29.520
and the head
of an organised criminal network.

23:29.640 --> 23:33.080
A relationship he will try to deny...

23:34.240 --> 23:36.520
...after the bonfire of all conventions.

23:37.640 --> 23:40.840
It also contains the names of MPs
who have signed up to the movement,

23:40.960 --> 23:43.920
and those MPs who are sympathetic

23:44.040 --> 23:48.440
but will not show their hand until
the organisation is announced officially.

23:48.560 --> 23:50.240
On 2 nd January.

23:52.000 --> 23:54.480
In Grosvenor House. You might want
to write some of this down.

23:54.600 --> 23:58.120
I am experiencing resistance
from my superior officers too.

24:03.000 --> 24:04.920
This isn't intelligence, Younger.

24:06.080 --> 24:07.720
This is evidence.

24:07.840 --> 24:09.280
Give it to the Branch.

24:09.400 --> 24:10.640
Special Branch?

24:10.760 --> 24:13.720
Half of whom spend their lives
defending the Union against Fenians,

24:13.840 --> 24:15.240
and the other half who spend their lives

24:15.360 --> 24:18.040
defending men like Mosley
against socialists.

24:18.160 --> 24:20.520
I heard about his speech
at your house the other night.

24:20.640 --> 24:23.040
Was favourably reported as
the passionate

24:23.160 --> 24:27.600
and spontaneous outpouring of a man
moved by the emotions of a ballet.

24:27.720 --> 24:28.880
Reported where?

24:29.000 --> 24:30.720
<i>Daily Mail. Morning Post. Daily Mirror.</i>

24:30.840 --> 24:34.040
It's upper, middle and working class,

24:34.160 --> 24:36.360
all united in admiration.

24:39.240 --> 24:43.200
Also, I'm being asked the source
of my information on Mosley.

24:43.320 --> 24:44.640
Which you don't divulge?

24:44.760 --> 24:45.960
No.

24:47.200 --> 24:50.280
And as a result, my six-monthly review
was unfavourable.

24:51.800 --> 24:55.280
They're talking about moving me to
a black and coloured desk in Johannesburg.

24:56.720 --> 25:00.040
I also suspect there are
specific threats to me personally

25:00.160 --> 25:03.440
from an organisation called Section D.

25:04.600 --> 25:06.880
I believe you've had a dispute
with them in the past.

25:08.960 --> 25:10.360
Sit down, Younger.

25:15.640 --> 25:17.320
(SIGHS)

25:19.040 --> 25:20.360
Yeech...

25:25.600 --> 25:27.400
We are now Section D.

25:27.520 --> 25:29.200
And I fucking beat them.

25:32.160 --> 25:34.720
You're a soldier, I'm a soldier.

25:34.840 --> 25:39.880
There are elements within the state
who are prepared to kill.

25:40.000 --> 25:43.080
We need to meet them unafraid.

25:46.680 --> 25:48.240
Spoken like a true believer.

25:50.440 --> 25:53.560
My superiors also ask why
the information on Jessie Eden

25:53.680 --> 25:55.760
and the Communists
has apparently dried up.

25:57.440 --> 25:59.440
Why has it dried up, Mr Shelby?

26:01.040 --> 26:03.080
Your sister has an interesting theory.

26:03.200 --> 26:04.920
She thinks perhaps at last

26:05.040 --> 26:09.480
Tommy Shelby has actually started
to believe in something.

26:20.040 --> 26:21.600
Younger.

26:23.600 --> 26:26.760
Please don't listen
to my sister's opinions of me.

26:26.880 --> 26:29.840
They are always...hopeful.

26:31.720 --> 26:33.440
Therefore they are always wrong.

26:42.280 --> 26:44.520
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

26:46.720 --> 26:48.760
(CHILDREN PLAYING)

27:54.400 --> 27:57.520
<i>(STEADY BREA THS)</i>

28:12.560 --> 28:14.000
Can you hear me? Look at me.

28:14.120 --> 28:16.120
You're going to be all right.
I'll be back.

28:16.240 --> 28:17.440
You'll be OK.

28:17.560 --> 28:19.000
Look at me. Look at me.

28:19.120 --> 28:20.360
It's OK.

28:25.400 --> 28:26.600
Fuck!

28:27.880 --> 28:29.200
Call an ambulance!

28:29.320 --> 28:30.760
Call Moss!

28:30.880 --> 28:32.640
Find out where I can reach Ada.
Come on, love.

28:32.760 --> 28:34.240
Up you get. Good girl.

28:34.360 --> 28:36.240
Come on, take her. Take her.

28:37.800 --> 28:40.920
Come on. Up you get. Up you get.
Good boy.

28:41.040 --> 28:42.200
Come on.

28:42.320 --> 28:44.720
In you go. Inside. Stay inside.

29:29.520 --> 29:30.680
(DOOR OPENS)

29:32.920 --> 29:34.480
(DOOR CLOSES)

29:38.200 --> 29:40.040
Tommy?

29:40.160 --> 29:41.400
Let's sit down, Ada.

29:41.520 --> 29:42.800
What's happened?

29:44.800 --> 29:46.560
Here, sit down, eh?

29:57.200 --> 29:59.080
Ben Younger is dead.

30:02.280 --> 30:04.200
Someone put a bomb in his car.

30:07.680 --> 30:12.160
I don't know how you felt about him
or how bad this is gonna hurt...

30:13.520 --> 30:16.440
...but whatever happens, just remember
you've a baby inside of you.

30:21.680 --> 30:23.400
Oh, God.

30:24.440 --> 30:26.800
Anyone you touch...

30:28.080 --> 30:30.000
Which means anyone I touch.

30:31.280 --> 30:33.280
Which means anyone any of us touch.

30:34.280 --> 30:36.520
He never knew I was pregnant.

30:37.800 --> 30:39.320
I hadn't told him.

30:41.040 --> 30:42.480
I didn't love him.

30:45.200 --> 30:46.640
But I liked him.

30:48.920 --> 30:51.560
He was decent and good...

30:54.400 --> 30:56.840
I wasn't gonna marry him.

31:00.000 --> 31:02.520
The baby was a mistake,
but that's OK.

31:04.760 --> 31:08.320
I didn't ask anything of him.

31:10.360 --> 31:12.840
God, he didn't deserve us.

31:16.680 --> 31:20.640
Well, I've spoken to his family -
they're gonna take care of the funeral.

31:21.960 --> 31:25.800
It will go down as an IRA assassination
of a British military officer.

31:28.920 --> 31:30.960
And what was it really?

31:35.960 --> 31:37.440
It was...

31:38.920 --> 31:40.920
...a consequence of good intentions.

31:42.120 --> 31:43.800
My good intentions.

31:46.080 --> 31:49.800
I pushed him to report on the fascists.
I thought it was the right thing to do.

31:51.120 --> 31:55.160
And as a result,
Section D or the Branch or Intelligence

31:55.280 --> 31:56.680
had him killed.

32:10.080 --> 32:11.760
There was a kid...

32:11.880 --> 32:14.040
...died in the explosion.

32:15.480 --> 32:16.920
He was ten years old.

32:18.320 --> 32:19.800
It's funny...

32:21.120 --> 32:23.320
...isn't it, how it works?

32:25.600 --> 32:27.880
- (CLEARS HIS THROAT)
- Look, Tommy.

32:29.560 --> 32:32.400
Don't give yourself this excuse.

32:36.760 --> 32:38.640
He was ten years old.

32:40.200 --> 32:42.280
If I'd have stuck to what I do,

32:42.400 --> 32:45.280
he'd still be kicking a ball
in the street.

32:48.480 --> 32:49.760
It's funny, isn't it?

32:55.120 --> 32:57.000
(DOOR CLOSES)

32:57.120 --> 32:58.760
(THUNDER RUMBLES)

33:00.600 --> 33:02.480
(SNIFFS)

33:13.240 --> 33:14.720
(SIGHS)

33:19.920 --> 33:22.080
<i>(STEADY BREA THS)</i>

33:47.240 --> 33:48.840
Push the button.

33:49.920 --> 33:51.960
Unlock the door and come home to me.

33:57.760 --> 33:59.400
(ENGINE STARTS)

34:14.120 --> 34:15.440
(ENGINE CHUGS)

34:15.560 --> 34:18.160
Chinese lanterns. Brass on deck.

34:20.720 --> 34:22.640
God fucking help us.

34:54.160 --> 34:56.960
ABERAMA: Chang will be waiting at the dock
with the cargo.

34:57.080 --> 34:59.760
We weigh it,
we load it, we fuck off.

35:15.920 --> 35:17.600
ARTHUR: Where the fuck is Chang?

35:25.080 --> 35:26.720
Isiah, take point.

35:28.440 --> 35:29.720
Look lively.

35:31.720 --> 35:34.520
CHARLIE: Right, there's your lanterns.

35:34.640 --> 35:37.040
Where the fuck are the Chinese?

35:37.160 --> 35:39.080
- ARTHUR: All right, Charlie.
- (COUGHING)

35:39.200 --> 35:41.440
Arthur, it's Chang!

35:42.680 --> 35:44.240
Christ!

35:46.400 --> 35:48.320
Get over! Get over. Get over!

35:49.720 --> 35:53.080
I knew we shouldn't trust these fuckers
and their fucking lanterns.

35:56.080 --> 35:59.200
(BULLETS RICOCHET)

35:59.320 --> 36:01.520
ARTHUR: If it's the police, hold fire.

36:01.640 --> 36:04.480
Chang, where's the stuff? Where is it?

36:04.600 --> 36:07.400
They didn't look like police.
Smelt of gin.

36:07.520 --> 36:10.520
They said they were taking the opium
on behalf of the King.

36:10.640 --> 36:12.240
Then they saw your boat coming.

36:12.360 --> 36:14.040
So, were they Italian?

36:14.160 --> 36:16.600
- Were they Italian?
- Irish.

36:16.720 --> 36:18.080
Irish, I think...

36:18.200 --> 36:19.560
Oh, fuck.

36:19.680 --> 36:21.760
Fuck! Charlie,

36:21.880 --> 36:23.160
my gun. Give me the gun.

36:23.280 --> 36:24.520
Give it up, that's it.

36:24.640 --> 36:26.600
Listen. Listen to me.

36:26.720 --> 36:28.680
They're Titanic boys out there, right?

36:28.800 --> 36:30.360
They're out of Poplar.

36:30.480 --> 36:32.920
In the war, they were very capable.

36:33.040 --> 36:34.840
Very capable soldiers.

36:34.960 --> 36:36.680
So was I.

36:36.800 --> 36:39.320
I was a fucking capable soldier, too.

36:40.640 --> 36:44.400
Hey! Hey, you fucking bastards!

37:03.160 --> 37:04.400
Arthur! Arthur!

37:04.520 --> 37:07.400
Stop firing! Arthur, they've gone.

37:12.400 --> 37:14.440
To any of you still alive,

37:14.560 --> 37:16.840
you do not fuck

37:16.960 --> 37:21.480
with the Peaky fucking Blinders!

37:23.800 --> 37:26.000
(HEAVY DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

37:28.880 --> 37:30.400
(COUGHS)

37:44.840 --> 37:46.400
Huh!

37:47.680 --> 37:49.000
Yeah.

37:52.280 --> 37:53.520
Here we go.

38:02.440 --> 38:03.800
Chang?

38:07.960 --> 38:09.240
Purest ever in Europe.

38:09.360 --> 38:10.520
Arthur?

38:10.640 --> 38:12.920
There's a dead man in a copper's uniform.

38:13.040 --> 38:14.600
Should I throw him in the cut?

38:15.960 --> 38:17.240
No.

38:17.360 --> 38:19.440
No, he'll float, won't he, eh?

38:19.560 --> 38:21.800
Even Irishmen fucking float.

38:22.920 --> 38:26.720
No, go and fire...go and fire the kilns.

38:26.840 --> 38:28.720
But there are men working them.

38:29.840 --> 38:33.680
Why do you carry a gun, Isiah, eh?

38:33.800 --> 38:35.400
And razor blades in your cap?

38:37.320 --> 38:39.800
Cos you're a Peaky fucking Blinder,
that's why.

38:39.920 --> 38:43.160
You take that body
and you burn it to the bone.

38:44.160 --> 38:46.600
And if anybody speaks to you on that...

38:47.560 --> 38:50.920
...you offer them the chance
to burn in that furnace with him.

38:52.040 --> 38:53.280
Right?

38:53.400 --> 38:54.560
Yes, Arthur.

38:55.600 --> 38:58.800
Yeah. Yeah.

38:58.920 --> 39:01.880
Do we know the people
who tried to trick us?

39:02.000 --> 39:03.200
The uncles will be mad.

39:03.320 --> 39:04.920
Fuck your uncles.

39:05.040 --> 39:07.280
And your aunts, your cousins,
all of them, right?

39:08.760 --> 39:13.680
Curly! Load this up onto the boat.
Let's get back to Birmingham, eh?

39:13.800 --> 39:16.400
Get back to fucking civilisation

39:16.520 --> 39:18.520
and find out who's been talking.

39:18.640 --> 39:20.320
Yeah! Now look,

39:20.440 --> 39:22.720
the Titanic heard about this, right?

39:22.840 --> 39:27.200
That means every gang from Poplar
to Birmingham will want to be here.

39:28.640 --> 39:30.400
Well, let 'em come, eh?

39:30.520 --> 39:33.000
Let 'em come, Aberama.

39:33.120 --> 39:34.440
Yeah.

39:34.560 --> 39:36.600
Oh, let 'em fucking come!

40:57.320 --> 41:00.560
(MEN'S SHOUTS ECHO)

41:10.840 --> 41:12.600
Hat and coat off.

41:24.520 --> 41:26.600
Stand up against the wall.

41:30.400 --> 41:33.480
For your own safety, I need to search you

41:33.600 --> 41:37.120
for items that could potentially
be used as weapons against you.

41:54.760 --> 41:56.360
Oh, that's nice.

42:15.880 --> 42:17.880
He was my friend.

42:18.000 --> 42:20.360
Yeah, well, he's nobody's friend any more.

42:20.480 --> 42:22.640
He's a fucking animal.

42:22.760 --> 42:25.240
Laces out of your shoes.

42:38.600 --> 42:40.120
Table.

42:42.840 --> 42:44.800
(KEYS JANGLE)

43:01.320 --> 43:03.440
(MAN SHOUTS WILDLY)

43:07.760 --> 43:09.720
Barney? Visitor.

43:10.840 --> 43:13.720
This one's real. (CHUCKLES)

43:13.840 --> 43:15.240
You can wait here.

43:15.360 --> 43:17.080
No. I can't.

43:25.560 --> 43:27.040
It's your funeral.

43:27.160 --> 43:28.840
- I'll have to lock you in.
- Yeah.

43:36.200 --> 43:38.240
- (DOOR CLANGS)
- (KEY TURNS IN LOCK)

43:42.520 --> 43:43.520
(CLANG)

43:48.800 --> 43:49.920
(CLANG)

43:52.920 --> 43:54.360
Hello, Barney.

43:55.360 --> 43:56.840
Arthur says to say hello.

43:58.960 --> 44:00.440
Sergeant Major?

44:01.960 --> 44:03.200
You're alive?

44:03.320 --> 44:05.400
Arthur's alive, John's dead,

44:05.520 --> 44:07.360
Danny's dead, Freddie's dead...

44:08.600 --> 44:10.960
...Jeremiah preaches the gospel barefoot.

44:12.600 --> 44:13.720
Yeah.

44:14.800 --> 44:16.000
And I'm alive.

44:20.080 --> 44:22.560
Them as have gone are the lucky ones.

44:26.040 --> 44:28.240
Thanks for the letters you send,
Sergeant Major.

44:28.360 --> 44:31.960
Yeah, Arthur mostly writes them.
I just...just sign them.

44:34.280 --> 44:36.920
How the fuck do you write back?
With your fucking teeth?

44:37.040 --> 44:38.760
No, they stick the pen up me arse.

44:38.880 --> 44:40.240
(CHUCKLES)

44:51.520 --> 44:52.920
(SIGHS)

44:53.040 --> 44:54.840
Someone in here said your name.

44:56.440 --> 44:59.240
They said
out there you are a politician now.

44:59.360 --> 45:00.880
Sometimes I am.

45:03.040 --> 45:05.080
I didn't know if it was real, comrade.

45:06.680 --> 45:10.160
I see rats coming out of bodies
like at the black wood.

45:10.280 --> 45:12.520
The shit they give me in here...

45:19.400 --> 45:21.040
Hey, Barney, look at me.

45:30.240 --> 45:32.320
Barney, this here is opium and cyanide.

45:33.320 --> 45:34.440
It'll bring on a heart attack.

45:34.560 --> 45:38.000
They won't even check the cause.
You won't feel a fucking thing.

45:43.960 --> 45:45.120
So, here.

45:48.440 --> 45:50.160
You're in here forever, brother.

45:51.640 --> 45:53.640
You don't have the use
of your fucking hands.

45:55.600 --> 45:57.360
You're still in the tunnels.

45:59.000 --> 46:00.680
I can give this to you now.

46:02.320 --> 46:04.160
Do you want it?

46:09.640 --> 46:10.720
No.

46:26.520 --> 46:28.120
Why not?

46:33.320 --> 46:34.760
I know.

46:37.240 --> 46:38.880
I know.

46:40.800 --> 46:42.240
You still remember...

46:42.360 --> 46:44.400
...that French waitress.

46:53.760 --> 46:55.720
You still going on about that, Tom?

46:55.840 --> 46:56.840
Yeah.

46:57.840 --> 46:59.360
Did you fuck her before me?
Because whoever did

46:59.480 --> 47:01.760
gave me the fucking clap.
But I'm guessing it was you.

47:01.880 --> 47:04.120
- Yes, I fucked her before you did!
- Yeah.

47:07.240 --> 47:09.160
- She was beautiful.
- She was.

47:09.280 --> 47:10.520
She was.

47:12.200 --> 47:13.200
And I reckon

47:13.320 --> 47:15.240
I was second best after Barney.

47:16.600 --> 47:18.480
Why did you bring the capsule, Tom?

47:18.600 --> 47:20.320
You're in here, Barney,

47:20.440 --> 47:23.680
you have no hands, there is no daylight...

47:24.960 --> 47:26.480
...and you don't wanna die.

47:27.600 --> 47:29.000
No, I don't.

47:33.720 --> 47:36.160
Because one day things might change.

47:45.760 --> 47:46.760
Yeah.

47:49.200 --> 47:50.880
Things might change.

47:54.120 --> 47:55.680
Maybe they already have.

47:57.840 --> 47:59.680
Come here, Barney.

48:00.720 --> 48:02.080
Come here.

48:05.280 --> 48:07.040
What if I could break you out of here?

48:08.120 --> 48:09.800
Why would you break me out?

48:11.320 --> 48:14.760
See, the trouble with the people in here
is the fucking meds they keep you on.

48:16.960 --> 48:19.680
Ten years since we were back,

48:19.800 --> 48:21.680
Barney, ten fucking years.

48:23.600 --> 48:25.000
Maybe the storm has passed.

48:25.120 --> 48:26.760
Passed for you, then, has it, Tom?

48:29.080 --> 48:30.960
What would the world do with me
if I was out?

48:31.080 --> 48:32.360
I've a job for you.

48:34.160 --> 48:35.080
Fuck!

48:35.200 --> 48:36.360
Barney...

48:37.840 --> 48:41.520
Barney, you were the best fucking sniper
in our company. Never missed.

48:42.840 --> 48:44.880
I can use that man.

48:45.920 --> 48:50.040
I'll get you the latest BSA,
fucking...telescopic sights.

48:51.200 --> 48:52.320
Who am I shooting?

48:52.440 --> 48:55.000
Fuck do you care, Barney?
Get that fucking thing off,

48:55.120 --> 48:57.360
- get you free.
- (BANGING ON DOOR)

48:57.480 --> 48:59.640
- Are you all right in there?
- Grand in here.

49:03.400 --> 49:04.920
What do you say, Barney?

49:05.920 --> 49:07.480
I'll come for you...

49:08.480 --> 49:10.520
...after midnight on Wednesday.

49:10.640 --> 49:12.240
I don't keep track of days, Tom.

49:12.360 --> 49:13.360
Don't have to.

49:13.480 --> 49:16.400
You'll know it will be Wednesday,
cos there'll be a big fucking bang.

49:17.400 --> 49:19.080
All right.

49:21.520 --> 49:23.520
(BANGS ON DOOR)

49:23.640 --> 49:24.560
Big fucking bang.

49:24.680 --> 49:27.680
- (DOOR OPENS)
- Big fucking bang.

49:27.800 --> 49:29.160
Big fucking bang.

50:10.000 --> 50:12.080
(EXPLOSION)

50:12.200 --> 50:14.360
(MEN SHOUT)

50:14.480 --> 50:15.960
It's fucking Wednesday!

50:18.760 --> 50:21.120
Big bang on Wednesday!

50:34.240 --> 50:36.120
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACH)

50:40.400 --> 50:43.040
They called from the Black Boy in Knowle.

50:43.160 --> 50:44.720
They'll be here any minute.

50:45.720 --> 50:47.800
I hear you agreed to give up the north.

50:49.360 --> 50:53.280
I hear...there needs to be
some certainty in the south.

50:53.400 --> 50:56.680
Some of my people were attacked
by members of the Titanic,

50:56.800 --> 50:59.040
who've heard about a cargo.

50:59.160 --> 51:01.320
Mr Mosley is open to suggestion

51:01.440 --> 51:04.240
regarding who he can rely on
to offer him support in London.

51:05.480 --> 51:09.880
Well, I would suggest the most competent
organiser of men in the south...

51:10.000 --> 51:11.920
...is Alfie Solomons.

51:12.040 --> 51:14.040
(LAUGHS) He's dead.

51:16.000 --> 51:17.360
And he's Jewish!

51:18.360 --> 51:20.960
And I'd say as far as
our boss is concerned,

51:21.080 --> 51:24.480
him being dead would be less
of an obstacle than him being Jewish.

51:25.880 --> 51:28.320
I think he'll give London to the Italians.

51:28.440 --> 51:30.600
He likes Italians.

51:31.960 --> 51:34.080
That'll mean more concessions
on your part,

51:34.200 --> 51:37.200
but you're going to have
to accept it, tinker boy.

51:39.360 --> 51:40.560
I like Wincanton.

51:41.560 --> 51:43.320
It's a grand old racecourse.

51:45.760 --> 51:46.840
And that brother of yours,

51:46.960 --> 51:49.600
the one who left me a hand grenade...

51:52.160 --> 51:56.080
...he'd be the first of you tinkers
I'd go for if our truce should end

51:56.200 --> 51:57.560
and the whistle blew.

51:57.680 --> 52:00.440
Good. He's in the mood for a quarrel.

52:03.880 --> 52:07.080
- We had a brush with the Titanic, Tom.
- Yeah, I heard.

52:07.200 --> 52:11.200
Yeah. Fun night. Got noisy, though.

52:12.520 --> 52:16.120
And to think they all said I was mad
to take me dad with me, eh?

52:16.240 --> 52:17.400
Your dad? Who's your dad?

52:17.520 --> 52:19.800
This is my fucking dad.

52:21.040 --> 52:22.840
Right here.

52:22.960 --> 52:24.520
This is my fucking dad.

52:24.640 --> 52:25.960
Where's Aberama?

52:28.000 --> 52:30.120
He got off at Solihull.

52:30.240 --> 52:33.360
Said if he sees Billy Boy here...

52:34.400 --> 52:36.480
...he'll cut his fucking throat.

52:36.600 --> 52:37.600
Tell the tinker

52:37.720 --> 52:39.800
he's welcome to come and try it
any time.

52:39.920 --> 52:41.200
Mm.

52:41.320 --> 52:42.480
Is it all aboard?

52:47.320 --> 52:48.480
Yeah.

52:48.600 --> 52:49.840
It's all there.

52:50.840 --> 52:52.480
We weighed it at the wharf.

52:52.600 --> 52:53.920
We used cockney scales.

52:54.040 --> 52:56.080
I wouldn't trust 'em.
They're probably crooked.

52:57.080 --> 53:01.000
- But, er, I reckon seven tons.
- Curly?

53:03.120 --> 53:04.360
Put ten sacks of flour

53:04.480 --> 53:07.280
- onto Mr McCavern's boat.
- Tom!

53:08.320 --> 53:09.760
I-I don't think it's really flour.

53:09.880 --> 53:12.160
I know, Curly. Just do as I say.

53:12.280 --> 53:13.560
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

53:13.680 --> 53:14.800
Curly?

53:19.840 --> 53:21.000
Hey, Arthur?

53:21.120 --> 53:23.520
Someday, yes?

53:23.640 --> 53:24.920
You and me.

53:25.960 --> 53:28.600
Oh, Tommy, hey?

53:28.720 --> 53:30.280
Fascists, hmm?

53:31.280 --> 53:33.080
Look at 'em.

53:34.080 --> 53:37.320
I fucking hate 'em. Always have done.

53:38.680 --> 53:40.520
But you...

53:40.640 --> 53:42.000
You, Billy Boy...

53:43.080 --> 53:46.480
...oh, you're special.
Y'know, I fucking like him, Tommy.

53:46.600 --> 53:48.480
I like yer.

53:48.600 --> 53:50.360
I do. You're a man after me own heart.

53:50.480 --> 53:52.520
- Someday, Mr Shelby.
- Yeah.

53:52.640 --> 53:53.760
- Someday.
- Yeah.

53:54.880 --> 53:55.960
Yeah.

54:02.160 --> 54:04.000
You just tell me when, Tom.

54:05.000 --> 54:06.520
You just tell me when.

54:09.360 --> 54:10.960
So, er...

54:11.080 --> 54:14.160
- ...so you spoke to Barney Thomason, eh?
- Yeah.

54:16.240 --> 54:17.640
Barney Thomason...

54:19.000 --> 54:20.560
...is gonna kill...

54:20.680 --> 54:23.880
...Oswald Mosley,
shoot him in the fucking head.

54:25.200 --> 54:26.200
Yep.

54:27.360 --> 54:29.000
While he's on stage.

54:29.120 --> 54:30.880
While I'm stood next to him.

54:32.480 --> 54:35.280
And then I will take over
as leader of the party...

54:36.320 --> 54:39.720
...and you and Aberama can take care
of that bastard McCavern.

54:41.400 --> 54:45.120
I had more complicated strategies in mind
for Mr Mosley.

54:46.120 --> 54:47.280
Then he spoke badly

54:47.400 --> 54:48.760
to my wife.

54:50.400 --> 54:52.640
It's going to be
a busy few weeks, brother.

54:52.760 --> 54:53.960
Yeah.

54:53.984 --> 54:58.984
http://hiqve.com/
